Examine a PHP function that accepts an array of numbers and returns the highest and
lowest values in that array. Display the results on the webpage.

ANSWER;
a simple PHP program that takes an array of numbers, finds the highest and lowest values using a function, and displays them on a webpage.

CODE:
<?php
// Function to get highest and lowest values
function getHighLow($numbers) {
    $highest = max($numbers); // built-in PHP function
    $lowest = min($numbers);  // built-in PHP function
    return array("highest" => $highest, "lowest" => $lowest);
}

// Example array
$numbersArray = array(45, 12, 78, 23, 56, 89, 34);

// Call the function
$result = getHighLow($numbersArray);

// Display the array
echo "Numbers in the array: " . implode(", ", $numbersArray);
echo "Highest Value: " . $result['highest'];
echo "Lowest Value: " . $result['lowest'];
?>

OUTPUT:
Numbers in the array: 45, 12, 78, 23, 56, 89, 34
Highest Value: 89
Lowest Value: 12
